The programming language for this computer is a custom assembly language made up of 11 instructions, each instruction executes a set of microinstructions to perform the operation.

Instructions:
NOP        -  No operation - Does nothing.
LDA(addr)  -  Load the contents of the given address into the A register.
ADD(addr)  -  Add the contents of the given address to the A register and store the result in the A register.
SUB  -  
STA  -  
LDI  -  
JMP  -  
JC   -  
JZ   -  
OUT  -  Output the contents of the A register to the 7-segment display.
HLT  -  
